CONCLUSION

The competitive landscape is a mirage.


Amazon Rufus, OpenAI Instant Checkout, Google UCP, Constructor AI, and Perplexity are all fighting for the same $15T mass-market shopping TAM. Accuracy, speed, and merchant fees matter in that market.


BuyAnything operates in a completely different market: $2-3B TAM of EA/FO procurement that has zero AI solutions and zero incumbent players.


The competitive threats are:



Not Rufus (locked into Amazon).

Not ChatGPT checkout (built for Shopify merchants, not EAs).

Not Google checkout (same issue).


Real threats:



Family office software companies (Masttro, Asseta, Aleta) launching procurement features.

Venture-backed startups targeting the EA/FO vertical with specialized procurement tools.

Luxury brands building their own AI shopping agents.


Defensibility window: 12-18 months. In that time, BuyAnything needs to:



Build a vendor network that's hard to replicate (relationships, trust, integrations).

Embed into family office workflows so deeply that EAs can't imagine working without Annie.

Establish brand credibility so that when competitors launch, they're seen as "also-rans" vs. the market leader.


The opportunity is real. The competitive risk is low. Move fast.



